group of players who banded together to form a permenant group.  We group together three nights a week on a regular, scheduled, basis.  Our current lineup is:<br>
<br>
44 duid<br>
45 enchanter<br>
43 cleric<br>
44 warrior<br>
45 paladin<br>
48 ranger<br>
39 shaman<br>
<br>
We also have a couple &quot;friends of the group&quot; who are currently in their low 40's (a mage and a necro).<br>
<br>
We have started to look for allies for large-scale raiding purposes.  The Saryn Guild Alliance seems to be exactly what we're looking for - a group of smaller guilds that get together to go on raids while allowing us to retain our own identity.  In return we bring to the alliance a ready-made group of mature, competant, group-wise players.<br>
<br>
We hope that you will consider us for membership.  In particular we noticed the regular Thursday night Kael raids and thought that this would be a perfect oppurtunity for us to get to know each other.<br>
<br>
Feel free to browse the chronicle of our adventures: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.furorpoeticus.org.">www.furorpoeticus.org.</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->  You may contact me personally at zaarain@eskimo.com or any of us in-game.<br>
<br>
-Gruffydd<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyriahwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myriahwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/7/01 4:22:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interested in joining SGA</span><hr size=1> Thanks for you nice post. <br>
<br>
We currently have 6 guilds in the SGA, and are not sure if we plan on adding anymore at this time. The best way to get into the SGA is to group with us. The thursday night Kael raid is a great opportunity to do just that. The more you group with our members the more likely they are to call for your guild being invited into the SGA. Sorry if that seems like a lame system, but it seems to be the one that works the best. Another thing that helps is to set up a relationship with one or more of our influential members (officers) with tells. Another thing you could do is run a multi-group raid somewhere and invite our members to attend. We have members of all levels, so we have many that could attend a raid you might run. Basically; the more good experiences we have with your guild the more likely we will invite you into the SGA.<br>
<br>
From my own perspective: I think you are the right kind of guild to join our ranks; small, experienced, and a good team. My misgivings are that you might expect to be ready to go to the planes and just pickup planes armor. The planes have been drastically buffed up, and are more designed for 54th plus level people. This means you are a long ways from being effective in the planes. Kael is a good warm up to get used to the way the planes are; hours of killing, little exp, little plat, and lots of deaths all for a small chance of obtaining something useful.<br>
<br>
Myriah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Anon Mike</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/9/01 6:38:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Interested in joining SGA</span><hr size=1> Actually I agree 100% with your concerns and we have similiar issues when it comes to expanding our own group.<br>
<br>
Tennyson (enchanter) and Paldaan (ranger) attended the Kael raid last Thursday and had a good time.  Paldaan and I helped Zargon take out Zephyl Saturday.  As a group were looking forward to attending other &quot;open&quot; events.<br>
<br>
Here's to a fruitful future for all of us!<br>
<br>
-Gruffydd<br>
